s been increasing since approximately 2001 and the most marked decreases in Campylobacter, Listeria, and Salmonella infections occurred before 2004. The incidence of STEC O157 infection in 2009 was similar to that in 2004.","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":592,"renderedHeight":346,"naturalWidth":592,"naturalHeight":346,"loading":null,"decoding":null,"altVerdict":"TOO_LONG","altReason":"alt text is 989 characters — consider a caption or description","bytes":12858},{"src":"https://www.cdc.gov/mmwr/preview/mmwrhtml/figures/m5914a2f2.gif","alt":"The figure shows the percent change in incidence of laboratory-confirmed bacterial and parasitic infections in 2009 compared with average annual incidence during 2006-2008, by pathogen in the United States, from Foodborne Diseases Active Surveillance Network (FoodNet) data.  In comparison with 2006-2008, the rates of Shigella (27% decrease, CI = 4%-44%) and STEC O157 (25% decrease, CI = 10%-37%) infection were significantly lower.","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":615,"renderedHeight":305,"naturalWidth":615,"naturalHeight":305,"loading":null,"decoding":null,"altVerdict":"TOO_LONG","altReason":"alt text is 434 characters — consider a caption or description","bytes":13080},{"src":"https://www.cdc.gov/TemplatePackage/images/icon_pdf.gif","alt":"Adobe PDF file","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":16,"renderedHeight":16,"naturalWidth":16,"naturalHeight":16,"loading":null,"decoding":null,"altVerdict":"GOOD","altReason":"present, no red flags","bytes":6058},{"src":"https://www.cdc.gov/TemplatePackage/images/icon_word.gif","alt":"Microsoft Word file","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":16,"renderedHeight":16,"natural